data.description:
Sellers will pay 10,000 toward buyers closing cost or interest rate buydown with an acceptable offer and will leave a 65' Samsung tv. Beautiful 4/2 on a generous .25 acre lot.  Located on the South side of town with a short ride Eglin AFB, Hurlbert Field and the areas beautiful beaches. You will appreciate the care and attention to detail that the 2nd owners have spent maintaining this property.  The expensive items have been replaced. New hot water heater, new garage door opener,  newer  architectural roof (2019), HVAC, and flooring. From the moment you step inside, you'll be greeted by an open and inviting floor plan that flows seamlessly from room to room. The large windows throughout the home allow natural light to pour in, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere. No association fees The kitchen is roomy with a large pantry, sit in dining area and island. The bedrooms are spacious and offer plenty of storage. The master bath is oversized with his and her closets.
Outside, the nice sized back yard provides ample space for outdoor activities and entertaining.
In the back yard, there is a double gate where an RV can be parked. Seller has a current survey and has had a termite bond in place since the home was first purchased.
